The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
The mhd_assert(c->read_buffer_offset <= new_buf_size) check is provably redundant: earlier the code tests if (c->read_buffer_size - c->read_buffer_offset >= need_to_be_freed) and sets new_buf_size = c->read_buffer_size - need_to_be_freed, which implies c->read_buffer_offset <= new_buf_size. Thus the assertion performs a runtime check that can never fail and has no effect on program behaviour; removing it would not change behaviour. As an executed, redundant operation it constitutes dead code and therefore violates MISRA C 2023 Rule 2.2.
